<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:141799" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera (Bothroponera) piliventris var. intermedia Forel" lsidName-HNS="Ponera (Bothroponera) piliventris var. intermedia Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="piliventris" subGenus="Bothroponera" variety="intermedia">Ponera (Bothroponera) piliventris Sm., var. intermedia</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="variety">nov. var.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="63">
- Les deux premiers segments de l'abdomen ont des sillons (et des cotes), mais faillies, surtout sur le second. - Long. 14 a 15 mill. - Sculpture du thorax comme chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:141759" authority="Mayr" authorityName="Mayr" class="Hexapoda" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bothroponera mayri Emery" lsidName-HNS="Bothroponera mayri Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mayri">B. Mayri</taxonomicName>
, reticulee-ponctuee, arec des fossettes espacees. C'est une forme intermediaire entre 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:186830" authority="Mayr" authorityName="Mayr" class="Hexapoda" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bothroponera piliventris (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Bothroponera piliventris (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piliventris">piliventris</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:2493" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ectatomma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ectatomma Smith" lsidName-HNS="Ectatomma Smith" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mayri</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageNumber="64" pageNumber="63">
[[ male ]]. Long. 11 a 12 mill. - D'un ferrugineux testace, avec l'occiput, le vertex et deux ou trois taches allongees sur le mesonotum seuls bruns. Scapes 2 1 / 2 fois plus longs que larges. Scutellum fortement proeminent en bosse subconique (arrondi en calotte de sphere chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:141850" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Bothroponera sublaevis subsp. reticulata" lsidName-HNS="Ponera (Bothroponera) sublaevis r. reticulata Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sublaevis" subGenus="Bothroponera" subSpecies="reticulata">sublaevis r. reticulata</taxonomicName>
) N oe ud du pedicule epais, fortement convexe devant et dessus, verticalement tronque derriere (surface tronquee tres luisante), tandis que chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:141850" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera reticulata Smith" lsidName-HNS="Ponera (Bothroponera) sublaevis r. reticulata Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublevis" subGenus="Bothroponera" subSpecies="reticulata">reticulata</taxonomicName>
le n oe ud est faiblement convexe a sa face posterieure. Ailes plus longues et plus jaunatres que chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:141850" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera reticulata Smith" lsidName-HNS="Ponera (Bothroponera) sublaevis r. reticulata Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublevis" subGenus="Bothroponera" subSpecies="reticulata">reticulata</taxonomicName>
. Tete, pronotum et mesonotum densement reticules-ponctues et mats. Le reste fortement ponctue et luisant. Mackay (Queensland), Turner.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
